TITLE: Opinion: The fatal flaw in 'Harry & Meghan'
SUMMARY: When Prince Harry and Meghan Markle announced in early 2020 that they were stepping back from their roles as "senior" royals, effectively quitting the royal family, they described a culture of familial tension, relentless scrutiny and certain misogyny. They no longer wished to be trailed by the media, obsessed over, watched. Harry didn't want to be constantly reminded of his mother's tragic death every time he and Meghan were photographed; Meghan didn't want to be tabloid fodder for what she wore, how she did her hair, where she was from or how much she did or didn't enjoy the spotlight. They wanted to reach financial independence, live as regular people, raise their children in private.
